<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
<title>The Lens — {{ manifest.url }}</title>
<style>
:root {
  --bg: #fafafa;
  --card: #ffffff;
  --border: #e5e7eb;
  --border-strong: #d1d5db;
  --text: #111827;
  --muted: #6b7280;
  --accent: #2563eb;
  --green: #16a34a;
  --yellow: #ca8a04;
  --orange: #ea580c;
  --red: #dc2626;
}
* { box-sizing: border-box; }
html { scroll-behavior: smooth; }
body {
  margin: 0;
  font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", system-ui, sans-serif;
  font-size: 16px;
  line-height: 1.55;
  color: var(--text);
  background: var(--bg);
}
a { color: var(--accent); text-decoration: none; }
a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
code, pre { font-family: ui-monospace, "SF Mono", Menlo, monospace; font-size: 0.9em; }
.wrap { max-width: 1080px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 24px; }

/* Top header */
header.top {
  background: var(--card);
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  padding: 32px 0;
}
header.top .meta { color: var(--muted); font-size: 14px; margin-bottom: 6px; }
header.top h1 {
  margin: 0 0 4px 0;
  font-size: 28px;
  font-weight: 600;
  word-break: break-all;
}
header.top .subtitle { color: var(--muted); font-size: 15px; }
.header-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr auto;
  gap: 32px;
  align-items: center;
}

/* Score circle */
.score {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  width: 140px; height: 140px;
  border-radius: 50%;
  border: 6px solid var(--border-strong);
  background: var(--card);
}
.score .num { font-size: 42px; font-weight: 600; line-height: 1; }
.score .lbl { font-size: 12px; color: var(--muted); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; margin-top: 4px; }
.score.s-ok { border-color: var(--green); }
.score.s-mid { border-color: var(--yellow); }
.score.s-bad { border-color: var(--orange); }
.score.s-poor { border-color: var(--red); }

/* Sticky TOC */
nav.toc {
  position: sticky;
  top: 0;
  background: var(--card);
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  z-index: 10;
  font-size: 13px;
  overflow-x: auto;
  white-space: nowrap;
}
nav.toc .wrap { padding: 10px 24px; }
nav.toc a {
  display: inline-block;
  padding: 4px 10px;
  margin-right: 4px;
  color: var(--muted);
  border-radius: 4px;
}
nav.toc a:hover { background: var(--bg); color: var(--text); text-decoration: none; }

/* Sections / cards */
main { padding: 32px 0 64px; }
section {
  background: var(--card);
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
  border-radius: 8px;
  padding: 24px 28px;
  margin-bottom: 20px;
}
section h2 {
  margin: 0 0 16px 0;
  font-size: 20px;
  font-weight: 600;
  display: flex;
  align-items: baseline;
  gap: 10px;
}
section h2 .layer-tag {
  font-size: 11px;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  color: var(--muted);
  font-weight: 500;
  background: var(--bg);
  padding: 2px 8px;
  border-radius: 4px;
}
section h3 { margin: 20px 0 8px; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 600; }
section p:first-of-type { margin-top: 0; }

/* Executive summary */
.exec ul { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; }
.exec li {
  padding: 10px 0 12px;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  display: flex;
  gap: 12px;
}
.exec li:last-child { border-bottom: 0; }
.exec li::before {
  content: "→";
  color: var(--accent);
  flex: 0 0 auto;
  font-weight: 600;
}

/* Tables */
table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 14px; }
th, td {
  text-align: left;
  vertical-align: top;
  padding: 8px 12px;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
}
th { font-weight: 600; color: var(--muted); font-size: 12px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; }
.kv { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 200px 1fr; gap: 6px 18px; font-size: 14px; }
.kv dt { color: var(--muted); }
.kv dd { margin: 0; }
.hint {
  font-size: 12px;
  color: var(--muted);
  margin-top: 4px;
  line-height: 1.4;
  max-width: 70ch;
}
.hint code {
  background: var(--bg);
  padding: 1px 4px;
  border-radius: 3px;
  font-size: 11px;
}

/* Rendered Markdown blocks (mostly inside .response and findings) */
.markdown { font-size: 14px; }
.markdown p { margin: 0 0 8px; }
.markdown p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
.markdown ul, .markdown ol { margin: 6px 0; padding-left: 22px; }
.markdown li { margin: 2px 0; }
.markdown h1, .markdown h2, .markdown h3 { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; margin: 10px 0 4px; }
.markdown strong { font-weight: 600; }
.markdown em { font-style: italic; }
.markdown code { background: var(--bg); padding: 1px 4px; border-radius: 3px; font-size: 12px; font-family: ui-monospace, "SF Mono", Menlo, monospace; }
.markdown pre { background: var(--bg); padding: 10px 12px; border-radius: 4px; overflow-x: auto; }
.markdown pre code { background: none; padding: 0; }
.markdown blockquote { border-left: 3px solid var(--border-strong); margin: 6px 0; padding-left: 10px; color: var(--muted); }

/* Score bars */
.bars { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 12px; }
.bar-row { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 160px 1fr 50px; gap: 12px; align-items: center; font-size: 14px; }
.bar-row .lbl { color: var(--muted); }
.bar-row .num { text-align: right; font-weight: 600; }
.bar { height: 8px; background: var(--border); border-radius: 4px; overflow: hidden; }
.bar > span { display: block; height: 100%; }
.bar > span.s-ok { background: var(--green); }
.bar > span.s-mid { background: var(--yellow); }
.bar > span.s-bad { background: var(--orange); }
.bar > span.s-poor { background: var(--red); }

/* Badges */
.badge {
  display: inline-block;
  padding: 2px 8px;
  border-radius: 999px;
  font-size: 11px;
  font-weight: 600;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  color: white;
}
.badge.b-critical { background: var(--red); }
.badge.b-high { background: var(--orange); }
.badge.b-medium { background: var(--yellow); color: #422; }
.badge.b-low { background: var(--green); }
.badge.b-ok { background: var(--green); }
.badge.b-warn { background: var(--yellow); color: #422; }
.badge.b-bad { background: var(--red); }
.badge.b-neutral { background: var(--muted); }

/* Persona cards */
.personas { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(320px, 1fr)); gap: 16px; }
.persona {
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
  border-radius: 6px;
  padding: 16px;
  background: var(--bg);
}
.persona .head { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: baseline; margin-bottom: 6px; }
.persona .head h3 { margin: 0; font-size: 15px; }
.persona .role { color: var(--muted); font-size: 13px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
.persona .quote {
  font-style: italic;
  border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
  padding-left: 10px;
  margin: 8px 0 12px;
  color: var(--text);
  font-size: 14px;
}
.persona ul { padding-left: 18px; margin: 4px 0 8px; }
.persona li { font-size: 13px; }
.persona .what { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 12px; }
.persona .what h4 { font-size: 12px; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--muted); margin: 0 0 4px; letter-spacing: 0.05em; }

/* Findings */
.findings .item {
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
  border-radius: 6px;
  padding: 14px 16px;
  margin-bottom: 10px;
  background: var(--bg);
}
.findings .item .meta {
  font-size: 12px;
  color: var(--muted);
  margin-top: 6px;
  display: flex;
  gap: 8px;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  align-items: center;
}
.findings .perspectives { margin-top: 8px; padding-left: 14px; border-left: 2px solid var(--border-strong); }
.findings .perspectives .p { font-size: 13px; margin: 6px 0; }
.findings .perspectives .p .src { color: var(--muted); font-weight: 600; }

/* Identity clarity 3-col */
.identity { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 16px; }
.identity .col {
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
  border-radius: 6px;
  padding: 14px;
  background: var(--bg);
}
.identity .col h3 { margin: 0 0 8px; font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; font-weight: 600; }

/* Page-blind queries */
.queries .q {
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
  border-radius: 6px;
  padding: 12px 16px;
  margin-bottom: 10px;
  background: var(--bg);
}
.queries .q .qtext { font-weight: 500; margin-bottom: 6px; }
.queries .q .response { font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); margin: 8px 0; line-height: 1.5; max-height: 6.5em; overflow: hidden; position: relative; }
.queries .q .response.expanded { max-height: none; }

/* Screenshot */
.screenshot {
  max-width: 100%;
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
  border-radius: 4px;
  display: block;
}

/* Methodology */
.method { font-size: 14px; color: var(--muted); }
.method ol { padding-left: 22px; }

@media (max-width: 720px) {
  .header-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  .score { margin: 0 auto; }
  .identity { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  .persona .what { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  .kv { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
}
</style>
</head>
<body>

{# ---------- Helper macros ---------- #}
{% macro score_class(n) -%}
  {% if n >= 80 %}s-ok{% elif n >= 60 %}s-mid{% elif n >= 40 %}s-bad{% else %}s-poor{% endif %}
{%- endmacro %}

{% macro impact_badge(level) -%}
  <span class="badge b-{{ level }}">{{ level }}</span>
{%- endmacro %}

{# ---------- Header ---------- #}
<header class="top">
  <div class="wrap header-grid">
    <div>
      <div class="meta">
        Run {{ manifest.run_id }} · started {{ manifest.started_at[:10] }}
        {% if manifest.actual_cost_usd %} · cost ${{ '%.2f' % manifest.actual_cost_usd }}{% endif %}
      </div>
      <h1>{{ manifest.url }}</h1>
      {% if classification %}
        <div class="subtitle">{{ classification.category_specifics }}</div>
      {% endif %}
    </div>
    {% if synthesis %}
      <div class="score {{ score_class(synthesis.composite_score) }}">
        <div class="num">{{ synthesis.composite_score }}</div>
        <div class="lbl">/ 100</div>
      </div>
    {% endif %}
  </div>
</header>

{# ---------- Sticky TOC ---------- #}
<nav class="toc">
  <div class="wrap">
    <a href="#summary">Summary</a>
    <a href="#fingerprint">Fingerprint</a>
    <a href="#scorecard">Scorecard</a>
    <a href="#audit">Technical</a>
    <a href="#pages">Pages</a>
    <a href="#identity">Identity</a>
    <a href="#page-aware">Page-aware</a>
    <a href="#page-blind">Page-blind</a>
    <a href="#personas">Personas</a>
    <a href="#convergence">Convergence</a>
    <a href="#divergence">Divergence</a>
    <a href="#recs">Recommendations</a>
    <a href="#method">Methodology</a>
  </div>
</nav>

<main>
<div class="wrap">

{# ---------- 1. Executive summary ---------- #}
{% if synthesis %}
<section id="summary" class="exec">
  <h2>Executive summary <span class="layer-tag">Layer 5</span></h2>
  <ul>
    {% for item in synthesis.executive_summary %}
      <li>{{ item | mdinline }}</li>
    {% endfor %}
  </ul>
</section>
{% endif %}

{# ---------- 2. Site fingerprint ---------- #}
{% if classification %}
<section id="fingerprint">
  <h2>Site fingerprint <span class="layer-tag">Layer 1</span></h2>
  <dl class="kv">
    <dt>Category</dt><dd>{{ classification.category }}</dd>
    <dt>Industry</dt><dd>{{ classification.industry }}</dd>
    <dt>Geography</dt><dd>{{ classification.geography or '—' }}</dd>
    <dt>Brand register</dt><dd>{{ classification.brand_register }}</dd>
    <dt>Evident goal</dt><dd>{{ classification.evident_goal }} — {{ classification.evident_goal_explanation }}</dd>
    <dt>Audience</dt><dd>{{ classification.audience_summary }}</dd>
    <dt>Audience segments</dt><dd>
      <ul style="margin:0; padding-left:18px;">
      {% for s in classification.audience_segments %}<li>{{ s }}</li>{% endfor %}
      </ul>
    </dd>
    {% if classification.competitor_examples %}
    <dt>Competitors (inferred)</dt><dd>{{ classification.competitor_examples | join(', ') }}</dd>
    {% endif %}
    <dt>Confidence</dt><dd>{{ classification.confidence }}</dd>
  </dl>
</section>
{% endif %}

{# ---------- 3. Scorecard ---------- #}
{% if synthesis and synthesis.score_breakdown %}
<section id="scorecard">
  <h2>Scorecard <span class="layer-tag">Layer 5</span></h2>
  <div class="bars">
    {% for k, v in synthesis.score_breakdown.items() %}
      <div class="bar-row">
        <div class="lbl">{{ k.replace('_', ' ') }}</div>
        <div class="bar"><span class="{{ score_class(v) }}" style="width: {{ v }}%"></span></div>
        <div class="num">{{ v }}</div>
      </div>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
</section>
{% endif %}

{# ---------- 4. Technical audit ---------- #}
{% if audit and audit.homepage %}
{% set hp = audit.homepage %}
<section id="audit">
  <h2>Technical audit <span class="layer-tag">homepage detail</span></h2>
  <dl class="kv">
    <dt>Render-mode JS-trapped</dt>
    <dd>
      {{ hp.render_mode_diff.js_trapped_pct }}% (raw {{ hp.render_mode_diff.raw_text_chars }} chars → rendered {{ hp.render_mode_diff.rendered_text_chars }} chars)
      <div class="hint">Share of text that requires JavaScript to extract. Hidden from non-rendering crawlers (some AI bots, RSS, traditional search). Modern AI assistants with rendering tools usually do see this content.</div>
    </dd>

    <dt>HTTPS</dt><dd>
      {% if hp.trust_signals.https %}<span class="badge b-ok">yes</span>{% else %}<span class="badge b-bad">no</span>{% endif %}
      <div class="hint">TLS encryption. Required by most browsers; lack of HTTPS triggers visible "Not Secure" warnings.</div>
    </dd>

    <dt>H1 count</dt><dd>
      {{ hp.html_structure.h1_count }}{% if hp.html_structure.heading_hierarchy_violations %} <span class="badge b-warn">{{ hp.html_structure.heading_hierarchy_violations }} hierarchy violations</span>{% endif %}
      <div class="hint">Pages should have exactly one H1. Multiple H1s or skipped levels (H1 → H3 with no H2) confuse screen readers and AI extractors trying to parse page structure.</div>
    </dd>

    <dt>Image alt coverage</dt><dd>
      {{ hp.html_structure.alt_text_coverage_pct }}% ({{ hp.html_structure.images_missing_alt }}/{{ hp.html_structure.image_count }} images missing alt)
      <div class="hint">Alt text describes images for screen readers, image search, and multimodal AI. Counted only over <code>&lt;img&gt;</code> tags — sites using SVG or CSS background images may show low counts without a real accessibility issue.</div>
    </dd>

    <dt>Low-quality link text</dt><dd>
      {{ hp.html_structure.low_quality_link_text_count }} occurrences
      <div class="hint">Links labeled "Read more" or "Click here" don't tell assistive tech, search, or AI agents what's on the other side. Each link should describe its destination.</div>
    </dd>

    <dt>JSON-LD blocks</dt><dd>
      {{ hp.structured_data.json_ld_blocks }} ({{ hp.structured_data.json_ld_types | join(', ') if hp.structured_data.json_ld_types else 'none' }}){% if hp.structured_data.missing_recommended_schemas %} · missing: {{ hp.structured_data.missing_recommended_schemas | join(', ') }}{% endif %}
      <div class="hint">Schema.org markup tells search engines and AI exactly what an entity is. Without it, AI assistants must mine prose to cite the page, which is error-prone. <code>Organization</code>, <code>WebSite</code>, and <code>BreadcrumbList</code> are the baseline.</div>
    </dd>

    <dt>Open Graph</dt><dd>
      {{ hp.structured_data.open_graph | length }} tags{% if hp.structured_data.twitter_card %} · twitter card present{% endif %}
      <div class="hint">Controls how the page renders when shared on social or in chat (Slack, iMessage, LinkedIn). Missing tags produce broken or generic previews.</div>
    </dd>

    <dt>llms.txt</dt><dd>
      {% if hp.llms_txt.present %}<span class="badge b-ok">present</span> ({{ hp.llms_txt.size_bytes }} bytes){% else %}<span class="badge b-warn">missing</span>{% endif %}
      <div class="hint">Emerging standard giving AI assistants a curated map of the site. Optional today, but signals AI-readiness.</div>
    </dd>

    <dt>Trust signals</dt><dd>
      contact {{ '✓' if hp.trust_signals.contact_info_present else '✗' }} ·
      privacy {{ '✓' if hp.trust_signals.privacy_policy_link else '✗' }} ·
      author byline {{ '✓' if hp.trust_signals.author_byline else '✗' }} ·
      last-updated {{ '✓' if hp.trust_signals.last_updated_date else '✗' }}
      <div class="hint">Basic credibility cues. Missing privacy / contact paths block enterprise procurement; missing bylines and dates make content harder to verify and cite.</div>
    </dd>

    <dt>AI crawler access</dt><dd>
      {% for bot, status in hp.ai_crawler_access.crawlers.items() %}
        <span class="badge b-{{ 'ok' if status == 'allowed' else 'bad' }}" style="margin: 1px 2px;">{{ bot }}</span>
      {% endfor %}
      <div class="hint">Per-bot rules from robots.txt. Disallowing AI bots prevents both training-data ingestion and (for some bots) live answer-citation in AI assistants.</div>
    </dd>
  </dl>

  {% if audit.site_aggregates %}
  {% set sa = audit.site_aggregates %}
  <h3 style="margin-top: 20px;">Site-wide aggregates ({{ audit.pages_audited }} pages audited)</h3>
  <dl class="kv">
    <dt>Avg JS-trapped %</dt><dd>{{ sa.avg_js_trapped_pct }}%</dd>
    <dt>Avg alt-text coverage</dt><dd>{{ sa.avg_alt_text_coverage_pct }}%</dd>
    <dt>Pages with H1 hierarchy violations</dt><dd>{{ sa.pages_with_heading_hierarchy_violations }} / {{ audit.pages_audited }}</dd>
    <dt>Pages with JSON-LD</dt><dd>{{ sa.pages_with_json_ld }} / {{ audit.pages_audited }}</dd>
    <dt>Pages missing privacy link</dt><dd>{{ sa.pages_missing_privacy_link }} / {{ audit.pages_audited }}</dd>
    <dt>Pages missing contact info</dt><dd>{{ sa.pages_missing_contact_info }} / {{ audit.pages_audited }}</dd>
    {% if sa.pages_not_https %}
    <dt>Pages not HTTPS</dt><dd><span class="badge b-bad">{{ sa.pages_not_https }} / {{ audit.pages_audited }}</span></dd>
    {% endif %}
  </dl>
  {% endif %}
</section>
{% endif %}

{# ---------- 4b. Pages crawled ---------- #}
{% if discovery and discovery.pages %}
<section id="pages">
  <h2>Pages crawled <span class="layer-tag">{{ discovery.total }} pages</span></h2>
  <p style="color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: 12px;">
    Discovery: homepage + nav/header/footer anchors + 2 levels deep, capped at 100 same-domain URLs.
  </p>
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>URL</th><th style="width: 80px;">Depth</th><th style="width: 100px;">Status</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
    {% for p in discovery.pages %}
    <tr>
      <td><code style="font-size: 12px;">{{ p.url }}</code></td>
      <td>
        {% if p.depth == 0 %}home
        {% elif p.is_anchor %}anchor
        {% else %}+{{ p.depth }}
        {% endif %}
      </td>
      <td>
        {% if p.status == 'complete' %}<span class="badge b-ok">ok</span>
        {% elif p.status == 'rate_limited' %}<span class="badge b-warn">rate-limited</span>
        {% else %}<span class="badge b-bad">{{ p.status }}</span>
        {% endif %}
      </td>
    </tr>
    {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
  </table>
</section>
{% endif %}

{# ---------- 5. Identity clarity 3-col ---------- #}
{% if classification or page_aware or page_blind %}
<section id="identity">
  <h2>Identity clarity</h2>
  <p style="color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: 16px;">Three independent views of the site's identity. The more these align, the clearer the page communicates.</p>
  <div class="identity">
    <div class="col">
      <h3>What the site says</h3>
      {% if classification %}
        <p>{{ classification.category_specifics }}</p>
      {% else %}
        <p style="color: var(--muted)">—</p>
      {% endif %}
    </div>
    <div class="col">
      <h3>What AI sees on the page</h3>
      {% set first_pa = (page_aware.values() | list | first) if page_aware else None %}
      {% if first_pa and first_pa.answers and first_pa.answers.one_sentence_summary %}
        <p>{{ first_pa.answers.one_sentence_summary }}</p>
      {% else %}
        <p style="color: var(--muted)">—</p>
      {% endif %}
    </div>
    <div class="col">
      <h3>How AI surfaces the brand unprompted</h3>
      {% if page_blind %}
        {% set first_pb = (page_blind.values() | list | first) %}
        {% set total = first_pb.query_results | length %}
        {% set mentioned = first_pb.query_results | selectattr('brand_mentioned') | list | length %}
        <p><strong>{{ mentioned }}/{{ total }}</strong> category-level queries mentioned the brand without seeing the page.</p>
      {% else %}
        <p style="color: var(--muted)">—</p>
      {% endif %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
{% endif %}

{# ---------- 6. Page-aware matrix ---------- #}
{% if page_aware %}
<section id="page-aware">
  <h2>Page-aware analysis <span class="layer-tag">Layer 3a</span></h2>
  {% for provider, response in page_aware.items() %}
    <h3>{{ provider }} <span style="color: var(--muted); font-weight: 400; font-size: 13px;">{{ response.model }}</span>
      {% if response.hallucination_flags %}
        · <span class="badge b-{{ 'ok' if response.hallucination_flags.overall_support_level in ['fully_supported','mostly_supported'] else 'warn' }}">{{ response.hallucination_flags.overall_support_level }}</span>
        {% if response.hallucination_flags.hallucinations %}
          · <span class="badge b-bad">{{ response.hallucination_flags.hallucinations | length }} hallucinations</span>
        {% endif %}
      {% endif %}
    </h3>
    <table>
      <thead><tr><th style="width: 30%;">Question</th><th>Answer</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
      {% for q in questions %}
        {% set ans = response.answers.get(q.id) %}
        <tr>
          <td><strong>{{ q.prompt }}</strong><div style="font-size: 12px; color: var(--muted); margin-top: 4px;">{{ q.id }}</div></td>
          <td>
            {% if ans is none %}
              <span style="color: var(--muted)">no answer</span>
            {% elif q.type == 'text' %}
              {{ ans }}
            {% elif q.type == 'list' %}
              <ul style="margin: 0; padding-left: 18px;">
                {% for item in ans %}<li>{{ item }}</li>{% endfor %}
              </ul>
            {% elif q.type == 'score' %}
              <strong>{{ ans.score }}/10</strong> — {{ ans.justification }}
            {% elif q.type == 'boolean_with_explanation' %}
              <strong>{{ 'Yes' if ans.value else 'No' }}</strong> — {{ ans.explanation }}
            {% endif %}
          </td>
        </tr>
      {% endfor %}
      </tbody>
    </table>
  {% endfor %}
</section>
{% endif %}

{# ---------- 7. Page-blind brand visibility ---------- #}
{% if page_blind %}
<section id="page-blind">
  <h2>Page-blind brand visibility <span class="layer-tag">Layer 3b</span></h2>
  <p style="color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: 16px;">Each query was asked of the model with no knowledge of the page. We then checked whether the brand surfaced unprompted.</p>
  {% for provider, response in page_blind.items() %}
    {% set total = response.query_results | length %}
    {% set mentioned = response.query_results | selectattr('brand_mentioned') | list | length %}
    <h3>{{ provider }} <span style="color: var(--muted); font-weight: 400; font-size: 13px;">{{ response.model }}</span>
      · <span class="badge b-{{ 'ok' if mentioned == total else ('warn' if mentioned >= total // 2 else 'bad') }}">{{ mentioned }}/{{ total }} mentioned</span>
    </h3>
    <div class="queries">
      {% for r in response.query_results %}
      <div class="q">
        <div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: baseline; gap: 12px;">
          <div class="qtext">{{ r.query_text }}</div>
          <div>
            {% if r.brand_mentioned %}
              <span class="badge b-ok">mentioned{% if r.mention_position %} · #{{ r.mention_position }}{% endif %}</span>
            {% else %}
              <span class="badge b-bad">not mentioned</span>
            {% endif %}
          </div>
        </div>
        {% if r.competitors_mentioned %}
          <div style="font-size: 12px; color: var(--muted); margin-top: 4px;">competitors named: {{ r.competitors_mentioned | join(', ') }}</div>
        {% endif %}
        <details style="margin-top: 8px;">
          <summary style="font-size: 12px; color: var(--muted); cursor: pointer;">view full response</summary>
          <div class="markdown" style="margin-top: 8px;">{{ r.response_text | md }}</div>
        </details>
      </div>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  {% endfor %}
</section>
{% endif %}

{# ---------- 8. Persona reviews ---------- #}
{% if persona_reviews %}
<section id="personas">
  <h2>Persona reviews <span class="layer-tag">Layer 4</span></h2>
  <div class="personas">
    {% for r in persona_reviews %}
    <div class="persona">
      <div class="head">
        <h3>{{ r.persona_name }}{% if r.persona_is_llm_lens %} <span class="badge b-neutral" style="font-size: 9px;">LLM lens</span>{% endif %}</h3>
        <div>
          <span class="badge b-{{ 'ok' if r.persona_satisfaction_score >= 7 else ('warn' if r.persona_satisfaction_score >= 5 else 'bad') }}">{{ r.persona_satisfaction_score }}/10</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="role">{{ r.persona_role }}</div>
      {% if r.persona_goal %}
      <div style="font-size: 13px; margin: 8px 0 4px;"><strong>Their goal on this site:</strong> {{ r.persona_goal }}</div>
      {% endif %}
      {% if r.persona_rationale %}
      <div style="font-size: 12px; color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: 10px;"><strong>Why this lens:</strong> {{ r.persona_rationale }}</div>
      {% endif %}
      <div class="quote">"{{ r.quotable_observation }}"</div>
      <div><strong>Goal outcome:</strong> {{ r.goal_outcome.replace('_', ' ') }} — {{ r.goal_outcome_explanation }}</div>
      <div class="what">
        <div>
          <h4>What worked</h4>
          <ul>{% for w in r.what_worked %}<li>{{ w }}</li>{% endfor %}</ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4>What failed</h4>
          <ul>{% for w in r.what_failed %}<li>{{ w }}</li>{% endfor %}</ul>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div style="font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); margin-top: 8px;"><strong>Next:</strong> {{ r.next_action.replace('_', ' ') }} — {{ r.next_action_explanation }}</div>
    </div>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
</section>
{% endif %}

{# ---------- 9. Convergence findings ---------- #}
{% if synthesis and synthesis.convergence_findings %}
<section id="convergence" class="findings">
  <h2>Convergence findings <span class="layer-tag">Layer 5</span></h2>
  <p style="color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: 12px;">Multiple lenses agree. Strong signal.</p>
  {% for f in synthesis.convergence_findings %}
    <div class="item">
      <div>{{ f.finding | mdinline }}</div>
      <div class="meta">
        {{ impact_badge(f.impact) }}
        <span>confidence: {{ f.confidence }}</span>
        <span>· sources: {{ f.sources | join(', ') }}</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  {% endfor %}
</section>
{% endif %}

{# ---------- 10. Divergence findings ---------- #}
{% if synthesis and synthesis.divergence_findings %}
<section id="divergence" class="findings">
  <h2>Divergence findings <span class="layer-tag">Layer 5</span></h2>
  <p style="color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: 12px;">Lenses disagree. Worth understanding which is right.</p>
  {% for f in synthesis.divergence_findings %}
    <div class="item">
      <div><strong>{{ f.finding | mdinline }}</strong></div>
      <div class="perspectives">
        {% for p in f.perspectives %}
          <div class="p"><span class="src">{{ p.source }}:</span> {{ p.view | mdinline }}</div>
        {% endfor %}
      </div>
      <div class="meta"><strong>Likely:</strong> {{ f.likely_resolution | mdinline }}</div>
    </div>
  {% endfor %}
</section>
{% endif %}

{# ---------- 11. Recommendations ---------- #}
{% if synthesis and synthesis.recommendations %}
<section id="recs" class="findings">
  <h2>Prioritized recommendations <span class="layer-tag">Layer 5</span></h2>
  {% for r in synthesis.recommendations %}
    <div class="item">
      <div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between; gap: 12px; align-items: baseline;">
        <div><strong>{{ r.title | mdinline }}</strong></div>
        <div>
          {{ impact_badge(r.severity) }}
          <span class="badge b-neutral">effort: {{ r.effort }}</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div style="margin-top: 6px;" class="markdown">{{ r.rationale | md }}</div>
      <div class="meta"><strong>Expected impact:</strong> {{ r.expected_impact | mdinline }}</div>
    </div>
  {% endfor %}
</section>
{% endif %}

{# ---------- 12. Methodology ---------- #}
<section id="method" class="method">
  <h2>Methodology</h2>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Discover.</strong> From the homepage, extract every link inside <code>&lt;header&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;nav&gt;</code>, and <code>&lt;footer&gt;</code> as anchor seeds, then BFS two levels deep from those (same-domain only). Capped at {{ discovery.total if discovery else 100 }} URLs. Junk filtered (search, login, cart, file extensions, pagination noise, tracking params).</li>
    <li><strong>Crawl.</strong> Raw HTML via httpx with browser-like headers, plus JS-rendered DOM via Playwright Chromium (waits for networkidle). Per-page artifacts saved to <code>pages/&lt;slug&gt;/</code>. Up to 5 concurrent browsers; failures on individual pages don't fail the run.</li>
    <li><strong>Audit.</strong> Pure-Python structural and technical checks per page: render-mode diff, heading hierarchy, alt-text coverage, JSON-LD validation, AI crawler robots.txt access, llms.txt presence, trust signals, page size.</li>
    <li><strong>Classify.</strong> One LLM call produces the site fingerprint (category, audience, goal, register, industry, geography, competitors), informed by the multi-page corpus.</li>
    <li><strong>Personas.</strong> One LLM call generates {{ persona_reviews | length }} review personas based on the fingerprint, including one LLM-as-reader lens.</li>
    <li><strong>Site-aware analysis (Layer 3a).</strong> Each enabled provider answers a {{ questions | length }}-question structured set with the multi-page corpus in the prompt.</li>
    <li><strong>Page-blind (Layer 3b).</strong> One synthesis call generates first-person seeker queries from the fingerprint; each query is then sent to each provider <em>without</em> the site content, and the response is post-processed to detect whether the brand surfaced.</li>
    <li><strong>Verification.</strong> A separate pass fact-checks each site-aware response against the corpus. Only unsupported factual claims are flagged as hallucinations; opinions and inferences are not.</li>
    <li><strong>Persona reviews.</strong> Each persona reviews the site in their voice, returning a structured score, what-worked / what-failed, and an in-character quotable observation. Prompt caching is used here: the corpus is sent as a cached prefix, so calls 2-N reuse the cache at 0.1× cost.</li>
    <li><strong>Synthesis.</strong> One final call takes every prior artifact and produces the executive summary, score breakdown, convergence and divergence findings, and prioritized recommendations for the site.</li>
  </ol>
  <p style="margin-top: 16px;">Generated {{ rendered_at }} by The Lens.</p>
</section>

</div>
</main>

</body>
</html>
